<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_d35409cd-8e51-49cc-b148-1e2a2f2ae8ae" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>3.3.3</sptc><title id="_509d54fb-5034-44e5-8b53-5346eb34c692">Surface water drainage</title><archive-num>2019: 3.1.3.3</archive-num><subclause id="_20f49fcf-1737-4cbc-b892-4153548ce89d" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_abac67c3-c415-4de6-bad4-e4a31aa853b0">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p><xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1486_26.5.0.xml#_02c3900f-c9bb-470b-93f4-d71555f2fea7" id="_51653b86-ed46-479a-bc0d-a22329fbb8a9" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">Surface water</xref> must be diverted away from a Class 1 building as follows:</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_fcb87230-37bd-48da-a02f-5490fe88a235">Slab-on-ground — finished ground level adjacent to a building: the external finished surface surrounding the slab must be drained to move <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1486_26.5.0.xml#_02c3900f-c9bb-470b-93f4-d71555f2fea7" id="_25f88f6a-10f9-45c2-a1a8-8668642cf654" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">surface water</xref> away from the building and graded to give a slope of not less than (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/536_0.8.0.xml#_dcf7d0d4-c5b2-40dc-ba13-ea6c95f510fa" id="_b2ab58c8-21e3-4926-a279-ae819bbd7cfa" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 3.3.3a</xref>) —<ol><li>25 mm over the first 1 m from the building— <ol><li>in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1364_3.8.0.xml#_6ff52a3c-f661-4540-bc88-52b7597794a9" id="_1f9f1a96-e570-4741-8b79-1e2958b9ebec" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">low rainfall intensity areas</xref> for surfaces that are reasonably impermeable (such as concrete or clay paving); or</li><li>for any reasonably impermeable surface that forms part of an access path or ramp provided for the purposes of <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/4994#_520db1d9-a633-4ac9-8c88-a960a99371f2" id="_91815e89-dfa8-43d6-aecc-6686aeab33cb" publishing-id="livable" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="standard-clause">Clauses 1.1(2)</xref> or <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/4994#_520db1d9-a633-4ac9-8c88-a960a99371f2" id="_cd750304-7bb2-491f-bb7c-5a1b2bef4a7d" publishing-id="livable" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="standard-clause">(4)(c)</xref> of the ABCB Standard for Livable Housing Design; or</li></ol></li><li>50 mm over the first 1 m from the building in any other case.</li></ol></li><li id="_f00c8db5-6c28-4890-ac45-483344dbccfd">Slab-on-ground — finished slab heights: the height of the slab-on-ground above external finished surfaces must be not less than (see <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/536_0.8.0.xml#_dcf7d0d4-c5b2-40dc-ba13-ea6c95f510fa" id="_d2b32b74-d549-4e51-9d39-e60690427a13" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 3.3.3a</xref>) —<ol><li>100 mm above the finished ground level in <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1364_3.8.0.xml#_6ff52a3c-f661-4540-bc88-52b7597794a9" id="_b8e9194e-c60b-4cd8-85fc-1ed90fb3fc54" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">low rainfall intensity areas</xref> or sandy, well-drained areas; or</li><li>50 mm above impermeable (paved or concrete) areas that slope away from the building in accordance with (a); or</li><li>150 mm in any other case.</li></ol></li><li id="_7fb047e8-5f30-42cd-968d-7c26ff6d9040">The ground beneath suspended floors must be graded so that the area beneath the building is above the adjacent external finished ground level and <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1486_26.5.0.xml#_02c3900f-c9bb-470b-93f4-d71555f2fea7" id="_e793663a-8ab1-4e05-a6ba-36abaff424fa" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">surface water</xref> is prevented from ponding under the building (see <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/537_0.6.0.xml#_3e6672e6-0b28-463c-9d08-3ed535847558" id="_98a42c75-d133-4991-93fa-d527677e8878" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 3.3.3b</xref>).</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_c7732183-d9d3-4e96-8875-d1f3d56f0370"><callout-type ncc-info-type="limitation"/><p>3.3.3 does not apply to a landing area provided for the purposes of Clause 2.3 of the ABCB Standard for Livable Housing Design, except for a channel drain or drainage surface provided under Clause 2.4 of that standard.</p></callout><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/536_0.8.0.xml" id="_dcf7d0d4-c5b2-40dc-ba13-ea6c95f510fa"><num xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" inv:access="external">3.3.3a</num><title xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" id="_778b510d-7c04-42f2-9b8b-6176a0748637" inv:access="external">Site surface drainage</title><image xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" alt="Site surface drainage" height="726" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:3-3-3a-site-surface-drainage.eps" inv:access="external" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/><desc-note xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" id="_4bed7983-c9f9-4df4-9913-dbeae4042bad" inv:access="external"><ol inv:access="external" outputclass="numbered"><li id="_e86a3ea0-dc13-492e-87c7-fa3f2a36530e" inv:access="external">For fall in finished external surface, see <xref format="dita" href="#_d35409cd-8e51-49cc-b148-1e2a2f2ae8ae" id="_a9cff5e1-96a0-4c50-9eee-106ea13ff815" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">3.3.3(a)</xref>.</li><li id="_c8f9ec94-37d4-4c17-b0ce-5ebfd1b826fb" inv:access="external">For finished floor level above finished external surface, see <xref format="dita" href="#_d35409cd-8e51-49cc-b148-1e2a2f2ae8ae" id="_9e88c68e-ae5d-4aae-ae87-63b4ca3672bd" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">3.3.3(b)</xref>.</li></ol></desc-note></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/537_0.6.0.xml" id="_3e6672e6-0b28-463c-9d08-3ed535847558"><num xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" inv:access="external">3.3.3b</num><title xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" id="_5e16e321-b1d9-4b00-8f87-eace28e64bdc" inv:access="external">Grading of ground under suspended floors</title><image xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" alt="Grading of ground under suspended floors" height="719" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:3-3-3b-grading-ground-under-suspended-floors.eps" inv:access="external" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/></image-reference><callout id="_a29480cd-c089-4b1d-b9ed-54f0bef46e2e"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>The appropriate slab height above finished ground level and the slope of the external finished surface surrounding the slab may vary depending on the following:</p><ul outputclass="alpha"><li>The local plumbing requirements; in particular the height of the overflow relief gully relative to <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1249_0.8.0.xml#_25307451-c7e1-4167-b4de-e5a1af26694c" id="_0a165c79-7bf1-491b-9c26-f10f3ecec7e3" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage</xref> fittings and ground level (to work effectively they must be a minimum of 150 mm below the lowest sanitary fixture).</li></ul><ul outputclass="alpha"><li>The run-off from storms, particularly in areas of high rainfall intensity, and the local topography.</li><li>The effect of excavation on a cut and fill <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_cd60ef8f-35d4-4249-8401-fe676a4225fe" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">site</xref>.</li><li>The possibility of flooding.</li><li>Termite risk management provisions.</li></ul><p>Clearances between wall cladding and the finished ground level are provided in <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1726_1.5.0.xml#_bf463061-ceb4-43cb-93dd-6cd4e2b1d050" id="_17b81280-a834-45e4-80cd-14212ef1c7ee" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="clause">7.5.7</xref>.</p></callout></clause>